      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 83: The reconnect path ignores high-priority call pushes when push notifications are currently disabled or `pushToken` is null. FCM messages can still be delivered after a settings/token transition, and dropping the restore/reconnect path here may cause an incoming call wakeup to be processed while proxy accounts remain inactive. If the intent is only to avoid leaving accounts active forever, keep the restore path for call pushes and rely on the recorded background-deactivated set plus final scheduling to restore/deactivate safely.\n```suggestion\nif (!appInForeground \u0026\u0026 app !\u003d null) {\n    val isCallPush \u003d isCallNotification || isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage)\n    if (isCallPush || (app.mPreferencesService.settings.enablePushNotifications \u0026\u0026 app.pushToken !\u003d null)) {\n        app.notePushReceived(isCallPush)\n        app.mAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n        if (isCallPush \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH) {\n            app.hardwareService.connectivityChanged(true)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
