      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 617: `restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()` removes an account id from `backgroundDeactivatedAccounts` even when the account is currently missing, disabled, or no longer proxy-enabled. If that state is transient during startup/account reload, the restore intent is lost and the account can remain inactive indefinitely. Only remove the id after a successful restore, or explicitly remove it only for terminal cases such as account deletion.\n```suggestion\nif (account?.isEnabled \u003d\u003d true \u0026\u0026 account.isDhtProxyEnabled) {\n    JamiService.setAccountActive(id, true)\n    backgroundDeactivatedAccounts.remove(id)\n}\n```",
